AIRHAMMER glanced over at UPROAR, his optics widening somewhat as he
saw him, but he otherwise said nothing.

On the other hand when BANTOR looked at UPROAR he glanced at him up
and down, &quot;You stand a good chance of infecting al the rest of us with
what ever it is that you have.&quot; he said as he backed up a pace. &quot;I
thought SANTON left you under BUMP&#39;s care at the Ark.

BANTOR smiled, &quot;Someone is definintly going to pay for that one.&quot;

&quot;You can keep an optic on the ship.&quot; AIRHAMMER said, breaking his silence.

BANTOR grunted, &quot;You have any disinfectant? We&#39;re going to need it
when we get back.&quot;

Part of what they were saying was good natureed ribbing, and yet part
of it was also concern for their comrade as well as how much he could
affect the health of the others on the mission.

